						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone in Survey No. 122.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription states that <hi rend="bold">Kēta,</hi> the son-in-law <hi rend="italic">or nephew</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Nāgaseṭṭi,</hi> constructed a tank to the west of <hi rend="bold">Negeyūr.</hi> It is also recorded that he was pierced to death by the thieves and that his mother <hi rend="bold">Mākabbe</hi> and his son <hi rend="bold">Hanuma</hi> erected the stone. The characters are of about the <hi rend="bold">11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
